text:
A good selection of Chinese vegetarian food with vegan options. Reasonably priced with friendly service.

** the other stall at Bukit Panjang Road ( Senja-Cashew CC ) is still in operation.
Simple vegetarian hawker fare, the bee hoon is nicely cooked without being too oily
Beehoon was tasteless, mock char siew was very tough, and popiah was super soggy. Prices was also quite steep.. not recommended as there are better vegetarian food around the area
Lots of vegetarian dishes to choose from when I went to get lunch. The queue moves steady as the uncle cooks while the aunty serves the line of customers.
For $5.6, I rather go next door for vegetarian food
